This paper deals with neural semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on using character-level translation to parse sentences annotated with Abstract Meaning Representations (AMRs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and related fields. 

The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as sequence-to-sequence models and pre-training, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper deals with optimizing the training process and improving performance, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
